WEBVTT

00:00:00.520 --> 00:00:02.580
<v Instructor>Now let's learn about Amazon Cognito.</v>

00:00:02.580 --> 00:00:06.540
So Cognito is a way for you to provide identity

00:00:06.540 --> 00:00:09.220
for your web and mobile applications users.

00:00:09.220 --> 00:00:11.700
So potentially you have millions of these users

00:00:11.700 --> 00:00:14.450
that are using, for example, your newest web application

00:00:14.450 --> 00:00:16.100
or your newest mobile application

00:00:16.100 --> 00:00:18.870
but you shouldn't create IAM users for them, okay?

00:00:18.870 --> 00:00:21.610
IAM users are only for the people who belong

00:00:21.610 --> 00:00:25.080
to your company and need to use AWS directly.

00:00:25.080 --> 00:00:27.920
Instead, what you can do is to create users

00:00:27.920 --> 00:00:30.660
for your mobile and web apps in Cognito.

00:00:30.660 --> 00:00:31.990
So this is a simplified version,

00:00:31.990 --> 00:00:34.060
but you would have Amazon Cognito

00:00:34.060 --> 00:00:36.420
which will have its own internal database of users,

00:00:36.420 --> 00:00:37.960
potentially millions of users,

00:00:37.960 --> 00:00:40.920
and then your mobile and web applications

00:00:40.920 --> 00:00:44.210
will have an integrated login into Amazon Cognito.

00:00:44.210 --> 00:00:46.490
Now Cognito is what you would maybe see behind some

00:00:46.490 --> 00:00:48.880
of these websites where you can also login

00:00:48.880 --> 00:00:51.230
with Facebook, Google, and Twitter

00:00:51.230 --> 00:00:52.660
by saying by click on the button

00:00:52.660 --> 00:00:54.380
and then you're redirected to Google or Facebook

00:00:54.380 --> 00:00:55.760
so it does that as well.

00:00:55.760 --> 00:00:57.480
So if you're thinking of building a web

00:00:57.480 --> 00:00:59.400
or mobile application and you want to have

00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:01.980
a way to mange users on AWS

00:01:01.980 --> 00:01:04.000
then Cognito would be the way to go.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:05.250
So that's it, I hope you liked it

00:01:05.250 --> 00:01:07.000
and I will see in the next lecture.